1
00:00:06,532 --> 00:00:10,668
These ... see, ślokas are reality.

2
00:00:10,668 --> 00:00:13,313
[Encapsulated Reality | Divine Poetry]

3
00:00:14,344 --> 00:00:17,746
Kṛṣṇa is siddhānta.

4
00:00:17,746 --> 00:00:20,505
They're not two separate things.

5
00:00:20,505 --> 00:00:27,036
Kṛṣṇa is siddhānta, siddhānta is Kṛṣṇa.

6
00:00:27,036 --> 00:00:33,059
The ślokas are encapsulated reality;

7
00:00:33,059 --> 00:00:36,115
they're real, they're alive, they're living,

8
00:00:36,115 --> 00:00:40,104
they're streaming real-time Kṛṣṇa conception.

9
00:00:40,104 --> 00:00:43,946
So Śrīla Gurudev, he liked so much

10
00:00:43,946 --> 00:00:46,538
the one verse from Gītā-govinda

11
00:00:46,538 --> 00:00:50,086
that appears somewhat in Charitāmṛtam.

12
00:00:50,086 --> 00:00:53,304
He liked to sing it sometimes. 
Like he told—what did he say?

13
00:00:54,989 --> 00:01:02,280
Manasa Krishna told, Gurudev said, 
"Good for hearing but not for telling",

14
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:04,861
like not explaining.

15
00:01:04,861 --> 00:01:06,851
But it's very beautiful, 
and it's mentioned that

16
00:01:06,851 --> 00:01:09,756
when Mahāprabhu would 
hear this He would faint.

17
00:01:10,594 --> 00:01:15,426
lalita-lavañga-lata-pariśīlana-komala-malaya-samīre

18
00:01:15,426 --> 00:01:21,281
madhukara-nikara-karambita-kokila-kūjita-kuñja-kutīre 
(Gītā-govinda: 1.4)

19
00:01:23,128 --> 00:01:27,741
So the beauty, as given by Jayadev Goswāmī,

20
00:01:27,741 --> 00:01:32,686
if you listen, the la-la-la-la-la, 
ka-ka-ka-ka-ka.

21
00:01:32,686 --> 00:01:41,401
lalita-lavañga-lata-pariśīlana-komala-malaya-samīre

22
00:01:41,401 --> 00:01:48,342
madhukara-nikara-karambita-kokila-kūjita-kuñja-kutīre

23
00:01:48,927 --> 00:01:54,504
This is divine sound and divine poetry,

24
00:01:54,504 --> 00:01:59,209
describing the beauty of Kṛṣṇa 
and the Pastimes of Kṛṣṇa.

